    <h4>Verdict</h4>
    <p><strong>pf-codemods makes zero package changes.</strong> This is a critical flaw — it applies PF6 API patterns (like <code>Content</code>, <code>labelHelp</code>, <code>hasBodyWrapper</code>) against PF5 packages where these APIs don't exist. The branch will never build.</p>
    <p><strong>semver/goose upgrades all PatternFly packages to v6</strong>, bumps React from 17 to 18 (required by PF6), adds <code>@patternfly/react-drag-drop</code>, and updates the <code>@openshift-console/dynamic-plugin-sdk</code>. Lockfile is updated with +1204 lines reflecting the full dependency tree.</p>
