<!-- PageSection -->
<details>
  <summary>📄 PageSection Variant Migration <span class="winner-tag">semver/goose wins</span></summary>
  <div class="details-content">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p><code>PageSectionVariants.light</code> is removed. Valid variants are now <code>"default"</code> or <code>"secondary"</code>. <code>PageNavigation</code> component was removed entirely.</p>

    <h4>pf-codemods approach</h4>
    <pre><code><span class="diff-del">- &lt;PageSection variant={PageSectionVariants.light}&gt;</span>
<span class="diff-add">+ &lt;PageSection hasBodyWrapper={false}&gt;</span></code></pre>
    <p>Replaces <code>variant={light}</code> with <code>hasBodyWrapper={false}</code>. This is <strong>semantically incorrect</strong> — <code>hasBodyWrapper</code> is a different prop that controls whether a body wrapper div is rendered, not the visual variant. The 8 resulting type errors confirm <code>hasBodyWrapper</code> doesn't exist on PF5's PageSection.</p>

    <h4>semver/goose approach</h4>
    <pre><code><span class="diff-del">- &lt;PageSection variant={PageSectionVariants.light}&gt;</span>
<span class="diff-add">+ &lt;PageSection variant={PageSectionVariants.default}&gt;</span></code></pre>
    <p>Correctly maps <code>light</code> → <code>default</code> per PF6 guidance. However, still produces build errors because <code>PageSectionVariants</code> enum may have changed shape in PF6. The mapping is correct per official docs.</p>

    <p>Both branches correctly remove <code>PageNavigation</code>.</p>
  </div>
</details>

